          .col-lg-6.order-lg-1
            .p-5
              p I spent the end of junior year learning about the technicals behind creating my first business. I read more IRS publications than anyone should ever even think about, I looked over tons of tax returns from the ultra-successful, and I carefully read federal and state return instructions to understand the ins and outs of tax law. Then, I committed to the tax laws by starting my own corporate entity. Finally, I dove into accounting and spent a ton of time learning about bookkeeping and financial record obligations. Because I already had experience in traditional financial markets, cryptocurrency economics, and real-world computer finance, this part came easier to me.
              p For full disclosure, I also own and operate MonerAds, LLC, a newfound alternative to advertising powered by blockchain technologies at #[a(href='https://monerads.com/') monerads.com].
